### Building a Custom Secure Verification API

Instead of paying high monthly fees for automation tools, you can run a custom, secure webhook receiver. Let me show you how to securely verify a payment signature using Node.js and Express.

This simple backend validation script ensures that nobody can spoof a payment confirmation and steal your physical or digital products.

```javascript
const express = require('express');
const crypto = require('crypto');
const app = express();
const paystackSecret = process.env.PAYSTACK_SECRET_KEY;

app.post('/payment/webhook', express.raw({type: 'application/json'}), (req, res) => {
  const hash = crypto.createHmac('sha512', paystackSecret).update(req.body).digest('hex');
  if (hash === req.headers['x-paystack-signature']) {
    const event = JSON.parse(req.body);
    if (event.event === 'charge.success') {
      // Process secure order logic securely
      console.log('Transaction verified:', event.data.reference);
    }
    res.sendStatus(200);
  } else {
    res.sendStatus(400); // Signature verification failed
  }
});
```

This setup verifies transactions securely in under two seconds. No visual templates, no hidden fees, and zero human confirmation lag.

### Eliminating the Subscription Trap

By coding direct API integrations, your business runs without relying on foreign subscription platforms. Custom hand-coded solutions mean your data is saved inside your own local database system, protecting your customer information from external breaches.

We build custom databases and WhatsApp conversational agents to process checkouts natively. No expensive friction, just clean code that works instantly.

